---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n';

const lang = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout title={t('nav.about', lang)}>
  <div class="container-narrow py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">{t('nav.about', lang)}</h1>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Mehdi Salem</strong> is a philosopher, critical thinker, and political-social analyst. As an independent researcher in analytical philosophy and ethics, his work centers on Iran's transition from authoritarianism to democracy and societal flourishing. Mehdi Salem takes an analytical and critical approach to examining fundamental questions in political philosophy, public ethics, and human rights.      </p>

      <h2>{t('about.education_title', lang)}</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>PhD in Public Policy</strong> (former candidate) — Tarbiat Modares University
          <br />
          <em>Thesis: "Developing a Model for Ethical Evaluation of Public Policies"</em>
          <br />
          <span class="text-text-muted dark:text-text-dark-muted text-sm">An interdisciplinary framework bridging analytical philosophy, normative ethics, and policy sciences</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Master of Business Administration (MBA)</strong>
          <br />
          <span class="text-text-muted dark:text-text-dark-muted text-sm">With focus on strategic management and organizational analysis</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>{t('about.research_title', lang)}</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Analytical Philosophy</strong> — Investigating foundational concepts through logical and linguistic analysis</li>
        <li><strong>Ethics & Moral Philosophy</strong> — Normative ethics, metaethics, and applied ethics</li>
        <li><strong>Political Philosophy</strong> — Theories of justice, democracy, liberty, and human rights</li>
        <li><strong>Public Policy</strong> — Analysis and ethical evaluation of public policies</li>
        <li><strong>Social Sciences</strong> — Political sociology and social criticism</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>{t('about.professional_title', lang)}</h2>
      <p>
        Beyond his philosophical and political research and writing, Mehdi Salem has professional experience in management and consulting. Drawing on his interdisciplinary knowledge spanning philosophy, management, and policy-making, he brings a comprehensive and multidimensional perspective to Iran's social and political challenges.
      </p>
 
      <h2>{t('about.mission_title', lang)}</h2>
      <p>
        Mehdi Salem's intellectual mission is to contribute to enlightenment and the advancement of public discourse in Iran. Through his analytical and critical books and articles, he seeks to chart an intellectual path for Iran's transition from authoritarianism to sustainable democracy. His writings are grounded in philosophical foundations while remaining accessible to the general reader.      </p>

      <h2>{t('about.experience_title', lang)}</h2>
      <p>
        Mehdi Salem is a former political prisoner of Evin Prison, with direct personal experience of the consequences of authoritarianism. This painful experience is not only his primary motivation for intellectual and written work toward freedom and justice, but also lends his writings a depth and authenticity that transcends purely theoretical analysis. He writes with a profound understanding of the real costs of the struggle for freedom.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
